hopobject.body: I'd like to cancel this standing order cheap renovations perth Clapper was technically correct that nothing has been put in place to specifically or deliberately spy on and target individual Americans. But news stories from the Guardian about both the PRISM operation at NSA, as well as the TEMPORA program that British intelligence agency GCHQ was using to tap into fiber optic cables, phone calls, Internet traffic, Facebook posts and emails – and which it was sharing in real time so that dozens of NSA analysts could sift through the massive data streams – paints a clear picture.
